owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Because objects of these types can be interpreted as numbers, they will be referred to as arithmetic types.

owl:Class.rdfs:isDefinedBy: Workflow to build code variants for the becnhamrks
Merge kernel-level and data-level features by outer-join

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The body of a function definition is a compound statement.
Declarations specify the interpretation given to each identifier; they do not necessarily reserve storage associated with the identifier. Declarations that reserve storage are called definitions.

A kernel is a function or subroutine of a program written in any programming languages. A kernel has a defined function body and can be executed on a computer. This is a generic concept used for performance analysis.

owl:Class.rdfs:isDefinedBy: Generate kernel based run for all the variants

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An Object is a named region of storage; an lvalue is an expression referring to an object.

owl:Class.rdfs:isDefinedBy: Adding the label of best-performing variants to the merged data
collect & sort time measurements from all variants and report the top varaiant for each each kernel and data input

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Primary expressions are identifiers, constants, strings, or expressions in parentheses. primary-expression identifier constant string (expression)

rdf:Description.rdfs:isDefinedBy: Description: we use nvprof to collect the data-level features. One example output from nvprof is https://gitlab.com/DATA-PLACEMENT-LDRD/optimization_unified_memory/-/blob/master/rodinia_3.1/cuda/nw/data-level-measurement/GPUTraceOutput_11_1024.log
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
Column description:
variable (array) name profied ,Profiled variable ID (varies by benchmarks),ID shows corresponding advise given,Input fro command line (size or input file name),The begin address of the profiled data on UM,The end address of the profiled data on UM,The profiled varialbe (array) size,CPU page fault count,GPU page fault count,Host to Device transfer (KB),Device to Host transfer (KB),Remote memory map (kb)

rdf:Description.rdfs:isDefinedBy: Description: the baseline kernel-level features were collected by nsight tool. One example raw report from nsight is at https://gitlab.com/DATA-PLACEMENT-LDRD/optimization_unified_memory/-/blob/master/rodinia_3.1/cuda/nw/kernel-level-measurement/nsight_needle_1024.log

rdf:Description.rdfs:isDefinedBy: Description: we run all the variants through nvprof to get the time measurement for each kernel. One variant example is https://gitlab.com/DATA-PLACEMENT-LDRD/optimization_unified_memory/-/blob/master/rodinia_3.1/cuda/nw/kernel-level-measurement/GPU-log/output_00_1024.log
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
Column Details:
kernel name,input from command line,advise for 1st data,advise for 2nd data,combination of all advises given in digits. Number of digits is same as the number of profiled data,precentage of time spent in this kernel (%),total execution time for this kernel(ms),# of kernel calls,average kernel execution time(ms) ,min kernel execution time (ms),max kernel execution time (ms)
